  "text": "In locomotion, it is known that the performance level, for example locomotor speed or jumping distance, is an important source of variation. Kinematic characteristics change with speed and a convenient solution is to add speed as a covariate in the kinematic analyses (e.g. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Swimming at a certain speed is not similar to performing at the same speed on land, however, because (1) the two media, i.e. water and air, differ drastically in their physical properties, and (2) the musculoskeletal system has to act against different substrates, namely viscous water versus solid ground.",
